<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB2211E5152DFF93FD825081F321FB36" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">
<treatmentCitation id="0A9310DA152DFF93FD825081F476FB0C" author="Lacordaire, J. T." box="[707,1034,1215,1236]" page="154" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" year="1866">
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FD825081F476FB0C" authority="Lacordaire 1866: 154" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityPageNumber="154" authorityYear="1866" box="[707,1034,1215,1236]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hemigasteraceae" genus="Hemigaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FD825081F34DFB0C" box="[707,817,1215,1236]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">Hemigaster</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA34B3A152DFF93FC785081F476FB0C" author="Lacordaire, J. T." box="[825,1034,1215,1236]" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" refId="ref5616" refString="Lacordaire, J. T. 1866. Histoire naturelle des insects. Genera des Coleopteres ou expose methodique de tous les genres proposes jusqu' ici dans cet ordre d' insectes. Vol. 7. Roret, Paris, France." type="book" year="1866">Lacordaire 1866: 154</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, not 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FB7B5081F325FB36" authority="Brulle, 1846" authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1846" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hemigasteraceae" genus="Hemigaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FB7B5081F4D4FB0C" box="[1082,1192,1215,1236]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">Hemigaster</emphasis>
Brull√©, 1846
</taxonomicName>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36CB152DFF90FD9A513DF09CFD92" blockId="1.[707,1194,1283,1730]" lastBlockId="2.[151,638,193,586]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="120" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FD9A513DF330FAC1" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" box="[731,844,1283,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FD9A513DF330FAC1" box="[731,844,1283,1305]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">Hemicolpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by Heller as a replacement for 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FC135120F448FAEB" authority="Lacordaire" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1866" box="[850,1076,1310,1331]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hemigasteraceae" genus="Hemigaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FC135120F3BCFAEB" box="[850,960,1310,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">Hemigaster</emphasis>
Lacordaire
</taxonomicName>
, which was preoccupied. The 
<typeStatus id="54898869152DFF93FC2F5107F3EBFA96" box="[878,919,1337,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FCF95107F45AFA96" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1866" box="[952,1062,1337,1358]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hemigasteraceae" genus="Hemigaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FCF95107F45AFA96" box="[952,1062,1337,1358]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">Hemigaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FB025107F355FAB0" authority="Lacordaire" authorityName="Lacordaire" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cubicus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FB025107F4D4FA96" box="[1091,1192,1336,1358]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">H. cubicus</emphasis>
Lacordaire
</taxonomicName>
by monotypy. Two additional South American species were described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA34B3A152DFF93FB525150F4D9FA5B" author="Hustache, A." box="[1043,1189,1390,1411]" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" pagination="201 - 208" refId="ref5550" refString="Hustache, A. 1932. Huit nouveaux Coleopteres (Curculionidae, Zygopinae) du British Museum. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, ser. 10. 10: 201 - 208." type="journal article" year="1932">Hustache (1932</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA34B3A152DFF93FD8251B6F28FFA45" author="Hustache, A." box="[707,755,1416,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" pagination="58 - 82" refId="ref5585" refString="Hustache, A. 1938. Zygopinae de l' Amerique meridionale. (Premiere serie.) Acta Entomologica Musaei Nationalis Pragae 16 (152): 58 - 82." type="journal article" year="1938">1938</bibRefCitation>
) and are treated below. In Heller‚Äô s (1895) key to the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FC10519DF3B5FA60" baseAuthorityName="Anzaldo" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[849,969,1443,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Conoderinae">Conoderinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FC99519CF43AFA60" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" box="[984,1094,1442,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FC99519CF43AFA60" box="[984,1094,1442,1464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">Hemicolpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the following combination of characters: eyes acute beneath (‚Äúteardrop-shaped‚Äù), separated by rows of scales; second antennal funicular segment subequal to the first; femora not carinate or armed with a ventral tooth; second abdominal ventrite strongly convex in lateral view (‚Äúarched‚Äù); and mesosternum even, without carinae and not excavated. This last character is not true of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FB2F5246F3A3F97F" authority="Hustache" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152DFF93FB2F5246F301F97F" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="119">Hemicolpus abdominalis</emphasis>
Hustache
</taxonomicName>
, but generic limits in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152DFF93FDA85293F31CF91A" baseAuthorityName="Anzaldo" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[745,864,1709,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Conoderinae">Conoderinae</taxonomicName>
are in great need of revision. In Anzaldo‚Äô s key (2017), 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FE2954FFF1ABFF0F" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" box="[360,471,193,215]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FE2954FFF1ABFF0F" box="[360,471,193,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Hemicolpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
runs to couplet 36 (
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FFDE54E5F109FF29" authority="Champion" authorityName="Champion" box="[159,373,219,241]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Helleriella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FFDE54E5F17EFF29" box="[159,258,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Helleriella</emphasis>
Champion
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FEC754E5F208FF29" authority="Heller" authorityName="Heller" box="[390,628,219,241]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cylindrocopturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FEC754E5F255FF29" box="[390,553,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Cylindrocopturus</emphasis>
Heller
</taxonomicName>
), both with quite different, usually relatively slender, elongate, and often smaller species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FD5B552EF0A6FE99" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Helleriella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FD5B552EF201FEFE" box="[538,637,272,294]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Helleriella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
possess femoral teeth, whereas femora of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FFD65578F114FE83" box="[151,360,326,348]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FFD65578F16DFE84" box="[151,273,326,348]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Hemicolpus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are unarmed. Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FFD6555EF146FEAE" box="[151,314,352,374]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cylindrocopturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FFD6555EF146FEAE" box="[151,314,352,374]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Cylindrocopturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus almost certainly not monophyletic, have unarmed femora, but some species (
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FFAD55A8F17BFE73" box="[236,263,406,427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">e.g</emphasis>
., 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FE5C55ABF0BDFE1E" authority="Champion" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cylindrocopturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulifer">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FE5C55ABF248FE73" box="[285,564,405,427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Cylindrocopturus triangulifer</emphasis>
Champion
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FFBF558EF201FE1E" authority="(Heller))" baseAuthorityName="Heller" box="[254,637,432,454]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cylindrocopturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ganglbaueri">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FFBF558EF25CFE1E" box="[254,544,432,454]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Cylindrocopturus ganglbaueri</emphasis>
(Heller))
</taxonomicName>
have carinate femora unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FE8555F4F24FFE38" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" box="[452,563,458,480]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FE8555F4F24FFE38" box="[452,563,458,480]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Hemicolpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Some 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FFD655DBF1F0FE23" box="[151,396,485,507]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cylindrocopturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FFD655DBF146FE23" box="[151,314,485,507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Cylindrocopturus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are more robust, have raised elytral intervals, and may be related to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D48152EFF90FFD65624F17AFDE8" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,262,538,560]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hemicolpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAD9152EFF90FFD65624F17AFDE8" box="[151,262,538,560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="120">Hemicolpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described here; genetic studies would be helpful.
</paragraph>
